Cluster bootstraps (`tables/loop014_h3_bootstrap_summary.csv`) show near-zero slopes at ≥$100k/≥$1M but a positive, if noisy, signal at ≥$10M; Loop 016 added the power summary + confirm shell (`tables/loop016_h3_power_summary.csv`, `tables/loop016_h3_confirmatory.csv`) showing a design effect of 14.8 (effective n≈978) and guiding the proposed single-test confirmatory family (`childhood_class_networth_ge10m`).

srs_justification: Two-test candidate family: (a) moderate practice × childhood class interaction (primary) and (b) serious practice × childhood class (supporting) on the ≥5 high-anxiety flag logit. Loop 020 extended the confirmatory shell (`tables/loop016_h4_confirmatory.csv`) to also report the 3-bin ordinal outcome and ran ridge (α=5) and ordinal stress tests (`tables/loop020_h4_stress_test_coeffs.csv`), showing the serious slope remains negative (p_ridge = 0.047, p_ord3 = 0.031). Benjamini–Hochberg control (m=2) therefore still favors keeping the serious contrast inside the proposed family while we finish reviewer sign-off.
